{"source_hash": "ae48c9df88c446c6", "candidate": {"id": "cand-013", "name": "Isabelle Fontaine", "raw_cv": "ISABELLE FONTAINE\nisabelle.fontaine@email.com | London, UK\n\nDATA ENGINEER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nData engineer with 4 years of experience in retail banking and insurance data platforms. Proficient in Python and SQL with growing experience in dbt and Snowflake. Good understanding of data quality and governance principles.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nData Engineer \u2014 Aviva, London (2022\u2013present)\n- Built and maintained ETL pipelines for the general insurance data platform in Python and SQL\n- Migrated 15 legacy Oracle procedures to dbt models on Snowflake\n- Collaborated with analytics team to improve data model documentation\n\nJunior Data Engineer \u2014 Nationwide Building Society, Swindon (2020\u20132022)\n- Developed SQL-based pipelines for mortgages data reporting\n- Supported data quality monitoring and alerting\n\nSKILLS\nPython, SQL, dbt, Snowflake, Airflow (basic), Oracle, Power BI, Git\n\nEDUCATION\nBSc Economics \u2014 University of Exeter (2017\u20132020)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nFrench national, EU settled status, indefinite right to work in UK", "raw_linkedin": "Data engineer in financial services. Four years building pipelines for insurance and retail banking. Growing expertise in dbt and Snowflake. I'm interested in moving into a more dynamic fintech environment from the larger, slower-paced corporate world. London-based with EU settled status. Open to senior data engineering roles where I can level up technically.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Isabelle, thanks for coming in. Tell me about your current role at Aviva.\n\nIsabelle: I've been at Aviva for two years. It's been good for building fundamentals \u2014 I've led a dbt migration project and we're now on Snowflake. But it's a large, slow-moving organisation and I feel I've hit a ceiling in terms of technical growth. I want to work somewhere where the pace is faster and the technical bar is higher.\n\nInterviewer: Tell me about your experience with event-driven architectures. We use Kafka heavily.\n\nIsabelle: That's an area where I'm still developing. I've consumed from Kafka topics for one pipeline at Aviva, but I wouldn't call myself experienced with it. It's something I'm keen to learn.\n\nInterviewer: And the office requirement \u2014 five days at Canary Wharf?\n\nIsabelle: I'm generally fine with that. I do think there might be some days I'd prefer to work from home, but I understand if that's the policy. I'm in Hackney so it's manageable.\n\nInterviewer: Salary expectations?\n\nIsabelle: Well, this is a bit tricky to answer precisely. I'm on \u00a360,000 now and I know I'd want to move upward. Something in the range of... I suppose somewhere around \u00a370,000 to maybe \u00a380,000? It would depend on the full package, the bonus structure, and other benefits. I'm not sure exactly what the right number is without knowing more.\n\nInterviewer: I understand \u2014 our range for this role goes up to \u00a385,000 for the right candidate. Do you have a sense of where in your range you'd need to land?\n\nIsabelle: Honestly I'm not entirely sure. Somewhere comfortable in that zone, I think. I haven't done a lot of salary research for this specific level.", "years_experience": 4.0, "skills": ["Python", "SQL", "dbt", "Snowflake", "Airflow", "Oracle", "Power BI", "Git", "Kafka"], "industries": ["financial services", "retail banking", "insurance", "fintech"], "seniority_level": "mid", "management_experience": false, "education_level": "bachelor", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.75, "culture_fit_score": 0.72, "constraints": [{"id": "f63d2743", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Current salary \u00a360,000; baseline reference point", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 60000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95}, {"id": "24ec3471", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Salary expectation range starts around \u00a370,000", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 70000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.85}, {"id": "e95bf128", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Upper end of stated salary range approximately \u00a380,000", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 80000.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.8}, {"id": "98ab1f46", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Employer role budget up to \u00a385,000 for the right candidate", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 85000.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.9}, {"id": "2ad93a67", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Five days per week in office at Canary Wharf required", "canonical_key": "office_days_per_week", "value": 5.0, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.88}, {"id": "2d2c2222", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Prefers some days working from home, but accepts 5-day office policy", "canonical_key": "office_days_per_week", "value": 3.0, "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.72}, {"id": "dbd1b992", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "work_arrangement", "description": "Seeks more dynamic fintech environment with faster pace and higher technical standards than current corporate role", "canonical_key": null, "value": "faster pace, higher technical bar", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.93}, {"id": "6d5bd13c", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "skill_development", "description": "Keen to develop skills in event-driven architectures and Kafka; currently limited Kafka experience", "canonical_key": null, "value": "event-driven architectures, Kafka", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.88}, {"id": "821d4aca", "ty